                            <comment id="13004697" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 18:21:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It turned out that the shared HTMLSchema instance introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-528&quot; title=&quot;Reuse tagsoup HtmlSchema instance across HtmlParsers (performance improvement)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-528&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-528&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was actually&lt;br/&gt;
not thread-safe as we assumed. To make it truly thread-safe, in revision 1079915 I enabled the ignoreBogons feature that prevents tagsoup from adding encountered unknown HTML tags to the schema.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004965" author="egh" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 05:06:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for fixing this!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
